article.headline: Boise St. 66, San Jose St. 51
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- La'Shard Anderson scored 18 points as Boise State won its seventh straight game with a 66-51 victory over San Jose State on Saturday night. Paul Noonan scored 12 points on four 3-point baskets, and Westly Perryman added 11 points for the Broncos (19-11, 10-6 Western Athletic). WAC scoring leader Adrian Oliver had 30 points for San Jose State (15-14, 5-11), which had a season-low point total and shooting percentage (29.1). The winning streak is Boise State's longest since the 2003-04 squad won seven in a row. After the Spartans got within 52-45 with under six minutes to play, Anderson made one of Boise State's 11 3-pointers. San Jose State got no closer than nine points afterward. Will Carter added 11 points for the Spartans.
